Influenza was estimated to account for a mean of 5,347 excess deaths per year (about 1.1% of the average annual all-cause deaths for the study period) in the Philippines over the study period, most of which (67.1%) occurred in adults aged ≥60 years (

  Table 2
 ). Influenza A accounted for 4,584 (85.7%) of all estimated excess influenza deaths. Although influenza B was estimated to cause fewer influenza deaths overall, it was responsible for about one-third (31.2%) of influenza deaths among 5−9-year-olds and one-fourth (24.1%) of influenza deaths among 0–4 year-olds.
